This query is slow because it repeatedly runs extra subqueries for every order. For each order row, the database must fetch order items and status history again. This repeated work makes the query much slower as the number of orders increases.
Identify specific parts of the query that are likely causing performance issues
The main performance issue is the correlated subqueries inside the SELECT statement:
The order_items subquery runs once per order
The order_status_history subquery runs once per order
These cause repeated scans of large tables.
